a MiniGL is just a subset of the OpenGL language - the matrix
functions, the rasteriser, maybe a few other little bits, but
with all the stuff like advanced texturemapping, bumpmapping,
and all that "useless" stuff taken out.

Therefore it`s slimmer, you can add your own super-quick versions
of OpenGL functions on top (if your texturemapper does a thing
a certain way only it will be fastre than OpenGL's which has to
take into account LOTS of variables and states)

You may as well just learn OpenGL

