Am 11-Sep-99 schrieb Bodmer Stephan:

Hi

>Is it possible to do some off-screen StormMesa rendering on a custom
>RastPort/BitMap and then blit it on the current screen/window ?

Actually in window mode StormMesa always uses an offscreen buffer for
rendering. The contents are finally transferred to the window when
the Swap function is called.

>I tried it but doesn't work... The StormMesa context is created, but no
>rendering are done (always a black screen, all GL functions doesn't seem to
>draw anything on my rastport). All my initialsation seems to be correct,
>because I could draw a RectFill on my custom RastPort and then Blit it on
>the front screen without problems...

>I created the StormMesa context with AMA_RastPort, &myrastport, and
>AMA_Screen, &wbscreen, like the doc says.

>What are the important point for off-screen renderings ?

The problem is most likely the double-buffering feature of StormMesa.
All new graphics drivers only support double buffering, so that
all drawings first go to a back buffer before they are blitted to
the destination rastport (when calling the Swap function).

If you switch off double buffering, GL should draw into the given
rastport, but BEWARE: it's slow, as the old graphics driver is chosen.
Additionally hardware support won't work.

Support for single buffering in the new graphics drivers might be
added in future, but right now I don't have much time to do it.
Please remind me about that feature, if I some day announced to
make a StormMesa upgrade.

