>all of GetMsg()/Wait() and result was unbelievable - about 20% speedup.
>I'll try to play with it to unfold a problem...

Why GetMsg() and Wait()? Basically you don't have to use the multibuffering
synchronisation feature, except if your game might run faster then the
vertical frequency of your monitor. StormMesa's triple buffering code doesn't
use any synchronisation, because almost no application achieves the
monitor's refresh frequency.

On the other side all those people using triple buffering should definitely
make sure either to limit the frame rate to the monitor's frequency or
use multibuffering synchronisation to limit the framerate. This should
have almost no impact on performance, if properly done (it's differently
programmed than double buffering synchronisation!). I wrote such a
swapping routine recently, so if anybody's interested I will provide it.

