@node 07928.001
Subject: Re: Rave3D
From: Paul Qureshi <paul@mc68k.demon.co.uk>
Date: Tue, 14 Sep 1999 19:03:38 +0100

On 13-Sep-99, cYBORG/iNDUSTRY wrote:

> Could anybody explain to me what's the point of using triple buffering
> instead of double buffering?

Simple. With double buffering your program has to syncronise screen
switching with the vertical refresh, so it may have to wait for that
time to come around before it can start drawing the next frame. With
tripple buffering you will always be able to draw to an off screen
bitmap unless you reach a frame rate equal to the vertical refresh
rate, not very likely in most cases.

Paul
