Alan Lee Maurice Buxey wrote:

> If I have a user defineable screen size, 640x480,800x600,2400x1800 ;-) etc
> how, within the code, is the best way to scale things to that size?

This depends on what you want to scale; if it's plain images, or 3D data.

For plain images:

You could theoretically use Warp3D to scale any image to the screen, but that
is limited by the texture size of the hardware. This is currently 512x512 on
the ViRGE (dunno 'bout the Permedia2), so this might not be an option if your
image is larger.

Second possibility would be to use a video layer, which would also restrict
yourself to hardware that supports this. Otherwise you have to use software
scaling like cybergraphics.library/ScalePixelArray

If you want to scale 3D graphics to the screen: Do it like OpenGL. Design your
transformations to work in unit space (i.e. -1..+1), and scale these to the
viewport before drawing. Check the OpenGL specs on how to do this.

Regards, Hans-Joerg.

