> so run a multiply function on the matrices..(?)

Something like that. Remember that device coordinates go from 0..width and
0..height respectively, while OpenGL/Normalized coordinates go from -1..1,
i.e. they are centered around the origin. To calculate the device
coordinates from normalized coordinates, do:

sx = width/2;
device_x = sx + x*sx;

and accordingly for the y coordinate. This assume you are using the whole
screen; if not, you have to offset the pixels.

